# Testing Strategy Concern Atom
concern: testing-strategy
triggers: ["test task active"]
load_when: task is test (auto-included)

## Coverage Targets by Scale
|Scale|Coverage|Required|Optional|
|------|------|------|------|
|Small (Q3.A)|70%|Unit tests|Integration tests, E2E|
|Medium (Q3.B)|80%|Unit + Integration|3-5 E2E for core user stories|
|Large (Q3.C)|90%+|Unit + Integration + E2E + Contract|Property-based, Mutation testing|

## Test Hierarchy
```
Unit → Integration → E2E → Contract
  ↓        ↓         ↓       ↓
속성 기반  스냅샷  시각적  카오스
```

|Layer|Goal|Key Rule|
|------|------|------|
|Unit|Coverage target|Mock ALL external dependencies|
|Integration|All core flows|Test containers or in-memory DB|
|E2E|5-10 core user stories|Full run under 2 min|
|Contract|Service interface verification|Consumer-Driven Contract (Pact)|

## Test Naming Convention
`given_<condition>_when_<action>_then_<expected>` or `test_<action>_<scenario>_<expected>`
테스트 이름은 검증 내용을 명확히 전달해야 함.

## Async Test Essentials
- Race conditions (concurrent access scenarios)
- Timeouts (async work completes within deadline)
- Deadlock detection
- Backpressure (slow consumer + fast producer)

## Language-Specific Test Tools
|Language|Unit/Integration|Async|Mock|Container|Property|
|------|------|------|------|------|------|
|Python|pytest|pytest-asyncio|unittest.mock, pytest-mock|testcontainers-python|Hypothesis|
|TypeScript|Jest/Vitest|built-in|Jest Mock, MSW|testcontainers-node|fast-check|
|Go|testing|built-in + `-race`|testify/mock, mockery|testcontainers-go|rapid|
|Rust|built-in|`#[tokio::test]`|mockall|testcontainers-rust|proptest|
|Java/Kotlin|JUnit 5|Awaitility|Mockito|Testcontainers|jqwik|
|C#|xUnit/NUnit|built-in|NSubstitute|Testcontainers .NET|FsCheck|
|PHP|PHPUnit/Pest|—|Mockery|—|Eris|
|Elixir|ExUnit|built-in|Mox|—|StreamData|

## Commands
`generate tests for <file/function> with coverage`:
Analyze → mock unit tests → async cases → measure coverage → run

`generate integration test for <usecase>`:
Flow analysis → dependency mapping → container setup → success/failure tests → report

`run tests and fix failures`:
Run all → collect failures → analyze root cause → fix → re-run until pass
